/*
=== MEDICINE TEMPLATE USAGE GUIDE ===

üìã REQUIRED FIELDS:
- id: Unique identifier (e.g., "med121", "med122")
- brandName: Commercial brand name (e.g., "Panadol")
- genericName: Generic/chemical name (e.g., "Paracetamol")
- description: Brief description of the medicine
- usage: Primary use and purpose
- symptomMappings: Array of symptom mappings (see below)

üìù RECOMMENDED FIELDS:
- dosageAdult: Adult dosage instructions
- dosageChild: Child dosage instructions
- dosageElderly: Elderly dosage instructions
- sideEffects: Possible side effects
- warnings: Important safety warnings
- priceRange: Price range in GHS (e.g., "GHS 5-15")
- category: Medicine category (see MEDICINE_ADDITION_GUIDE.md for list)
- drugClass: Drug class (see MEDICINE_ADDITION_GUIDE.md for list)
- prescription: true/false (requires prescription?)
- controlled: true/false (controlled substance?)

üîó SYMPTOM MAPPINGS:
Each mapping must include:
- symptomId: MUST match an ID from /public/symptoms.json
- effectivenessScore: 1-10 (1=poor, 10=excellent)
- isPrimary: true/false (primary use for this medicine?)
- evidenceLevel: "Strong", "Moderate", "Weak", or "Theoretical"
- notes: Additional effectiveness notes

üìã EXAMPLE SYMPTOM MAPPING:
{
  "symptomId": "fever",
  "effectivenessScore": 9,
  "isPrimary": true,
  "evidenceLevel": "Strong",
  "notes": "First-line treatment for fever"
}

üè∑Ô∏è CATEGORIES (choose one):
"Allergy", "Antibiotic", "Antimalarial", "Antiparasitic", "Anxiety",
"Cardiovascular", "Cold & Allergy", "Cough & Cold", "Diabetes", "Digestive",
"Herbal", "Pain Relief", "Respiratory", "Supplement", "Vitamin"

üíä DRUG CLASSES (examples):
